    definition: `A quantum attack where the adversary sees your public key in the mempool (during the ~10 minutes between broadcast and confirmation) and cracks your ECDSA private key before your transaction confirms. The attack window is ~10 minutes. Current quantum computers cannot crack ECDSA in 10 minutes. Google targets this capability by 2029`,
